^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now one point on the play of the hand. With a 9 card fit missing the Queen, the conventional wisdom is to play for the drop. However the conventional wisdom is wrong most of the time. Given no information in the auction, playing for the drop is only very slightly better than taking the finesse (51 or 52% vs. 50%). |
PG| ***** 53 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|But you often have information in the auction. On this hand, Kia has shown 2 suits. So Babs knows 9 or more of Kia's cards are not in hearts. Therefore, it is much more likely that I have the @HQ than Kia. In fact it is quite possible Kia has a singleton. So Babs should play the @HK and then finesse the @HJ and make the hand.|
